  valid until 2031. Public copy at `admin.majicholdings.com/MajicCodeSigning.cer`.
  GPO pushes it to **Trusted Root + Trusted Publishers** domain-wide, so
  internally-signed binaries don't trip SmartScreen.

## Secrets — Google Secret Manager

GSM project `micro-enigma-494403-d0` is the **source of truth** for all
integration secrets. The `gcc-api` reads them at startup via
`SecretManagerConfig.cs` (custom `IConfigurationProvider`, registered in
`Program.cs` immediately after `WebApplication.CreateBuilder` so it has
highest precedence). `appsettings.json` is gitignored everywhere and only
holds non-secret bootstrap pointers.

Local mirror: `$HOME\.gcc-secrets\` (ACL'd to Administrator + SYSTEM).

- `sync-from-gsm.py` — pull all 95 GSM secrets to `gsm.json` and `gsm.env`.
- `Load-GccSecrets.ps1` — source `gsm.json` into a pwsh session as `$env:`
  vars. Often auto-loaded via `$PROFILE`.

**Key gotcha — `Bc:ClientSecret` reuses `infra-aps-client-secret`** (same
Autodesk APS app per `Bc.cs`). Don't add a parallel `admin-bc-client-secret`
— the two would just drift.

Full secret-ID → config-key map and the rest of the architecture lives at
`C:\Users\Administrator.greencommcont\.claude\projects\C--\memory\gcc_secrets.md`.

